news.title: Chicago residents to vote on real estate tax hike
news.para: The ballot measure would lower property transfer taxes for the vast majority of Chicago residents, to $3 for every $500 of a transfer price under $1 million, down from the current flat rate of $3.75.

news.title: Signa creditors back restructuring plan to avert fire sale of top assets
news.para: Signa, the Austrian property empire founded by Rene Benko, has become the biggest casualty so far in Europe's real estate crisis, with creditors filing claims totalling billions of euros.

news.title: India's buildings sector to overshoot country's entire carbon budget: Report
news.para: The countries are striving to achieve net-zero emissions (a balance between greenhouse gases emitted and removed from the atmosphere) to limit the rise in global average temperatures to 1.5 degrees Celsius and prevent further worsening of climate impacts.
